  "chapter": {
    "number": 44,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "The LORD Has Chosen Israel"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "But now listen, O Jacob My servant,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Israel, whom I have chosen.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "This is the word of the LORD, your Maker,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "who formed you from the womb and who will help you:",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "“Do not be afraid, O Jacob My servant,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Jeshurun,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2667
          },
          {
            "text": "whom I have chosen.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For I will pour water on the thirsty land,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and currents on the dry ground.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I will pour out My Spirit on your descendants,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and My blessing on your offspring.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "They will sprout among the grass",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "like willows",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2668
          },
          {
            "text": "by flowing streams.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "One will say, ‘I belong to the LORD,’",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "another will call himself by the name of Jacob,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and still another will write on his hand, ‘The LORD’s,’",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and will take the name of Israel.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Thus says the LORD,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the King and Redeemer of Israel, the LORD of Hosts:",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“I am the first and I am the last,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and there is no God but Me.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Who then is like Me?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Let him say so!",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Let him declare his case before Me,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "since I established an ancient people.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Let him foretell the things to come,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and what is to take place.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Do not tremble or fear.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Have I not told you and declared it long ago?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "You are My witnesses!",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Is there any God but Me?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "There is no other Rock;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I know not one.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "All makers of idols are nothing,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the things they treasure are worthless.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Their witnesses fail to see or comprehend,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "so they are put to shame.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Who fashions a god or casts an idol",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "which profits him nothing?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Behold, all his companions will be put to shame,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "for the craftsmen themselves are only human.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Let them all assemble and take their stand;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they will all be brought to terror and shame.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The blacksmith takes a tool",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and labors over the coals;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "he fashions an idol with hammers",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and forges it with his strong arms.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Yet he grows hungry and loses his strength;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "he fails to drink water and grows faint.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The woodworker extends a measuring line;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "he marks it out with a stylus;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "he shapes it with chisels",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and outlines it with a compass.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "He fashions it in the likeness of man,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "like man in all his glory,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "that it may dwell in a shrine.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He cuts down cedars",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "or retrieves a cypress",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2669
          },
          {
            "text": "or oak.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "He lets it grow strong among the trees of the forest.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He plants a laurel, and the rain makes it grow.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "It serves as fuel for man.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He takes some of it to warm himself,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and he kindles a fire",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and bakes his bread;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "he even fashions it into a god and worships it;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "he makes an idol and bows down to it.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He burns half of it in the fire,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and he roasts meat on that half.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "He eats the roast and is satisfied.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Indeed, he warms himself and says,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "“Ah! I am warm; I see the fire.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "From the rest he makes a god, his graven image.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He bows down to it and worships;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "he prays to it and says,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "“Save me, for you are my god.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "They do not comprehend or discern,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "for He has shut their eyes so they cannot see",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and closed their minds so they cannot understand.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "And no one considers in his heart,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "no one has the knowledge or insight to say,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "“I burned half of it in the fire,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and I baked bread on its coals;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I roasted meat and I ate.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Shall I make something detestable with the rest of it?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Shall I bow down to a block of wood?”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He feeds on ashes.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "His deluded heart has led him astray,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and he cannot deliver himself or say,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "“Is not this thing in my right hand a lie?”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Jerusalem to Be Restored"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 21,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Remember these things, O Jacob,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "for you are My servant, O Israel.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I have made you, and you are My servant;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "O Israel, I will never forget you.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 22,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I have blotted out your transgressions like a cloud,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and your sins like a mist.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Return to Me, for I have redeemed you.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 23,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Sing for joy, O heavens, for the LORD has done this;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "shout aloud, O depths of the earth.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Break forth in song, O mountains,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "you forests and all your trees.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "For the LORD has redeemed Jacob,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and revealed His glory in Israel.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 24,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Thus says the LORD,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "your Redeemer who formed you from the womb:",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“I am the LORD,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "who has made all things,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "who alone stretched out the heavens,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "who by Myself spread out the earth,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 25,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "who foils the signs of false prophets",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and makes fools of diviners,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "who confounds the wise",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and turns their knowledge into nonsense,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 26,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "who confirms the message of His servant",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and fulfills the counsel of His messengers,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "who says of Jerusalem,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "‘She will be inhabited,’",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and of the cities of Judah,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "‘They will be rebuilt, and I will restore their ruins,’",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 27,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "who says to the depths of the sea,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "‘Be dry, and I will dry up your currents,’",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 28,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "who says of Cyrus,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "‘My shepherd will fulfill all that I desire,’",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "who says of Jerusalem,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "‘She will be rebuilt,’",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and of the temple,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "‘Let its foundation be laid.’”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
